<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-524-038  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 524 038.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  July 11 1989* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Database retrieval breakthrough.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Takahashi, Ken.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   NEC Corp. (product development).andO;Topic:     Natural Language InterfacesData base management systemsInformation Storage and RetrievalForeign LanguagesJapanese LanguageProduct Development.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>DATABASE RETRIEVAL BREAKTHROUGH TOKYO, JAPAN, 1989 JUN 29 (NB) -- NEC hasdeveloped software which will enable the development of a database retrievalsystem that responds to the keyboard input of natural language sentences inJapanese.andP;  Extensive programming to incorporate a database of grammar andJapanese vocabulary used to be necessary to develop programs such as this.andO;But NEC's software adopts a new method called &quot;grammar analysis using examplesentences,&quot; which enables the process to be far speedier on a workstation.andO;According to NEC's calculations, development of similar systems, which usedto take over a year, could take one or two months using the new software.andO;(Ken Takahashi/19890706)</TEXT></DOC>